<br>
I had my play account accidentally have a GM flag on it in regard to factions being shown as numerics or standard temporarily in the early days of the game(and until it was fixed, my guide account on another server was minus that ability), and unless it applies in INSANELY small amounts I can say unequivocally it does not exist... whenever my faction hit the same numeric with a 75 CHA necro as my 127 CHA bard the factions reported with /con were identical, and always matched up 100 percent to the numerics that were given by the server... note however, the biggest hit I remember getting the entire time was around +10, so maybe it only appears in higher instances but I find it HIGHLY doubtful....<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=pilferer>Pilferer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/6/02 9:54:35 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22091.topic&index=27>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> A thought</span><hr size=1> I was under the impression that the faction was a -XXX to +XXX pure number for everyone.  And race/religion has a shift on this scale vs each faction.  ie: for a different character on the same mob, the indiff/apprehensive border might lie at -400 if a critter naturally likes high elves and at +300 if the critter naturally hates trolls, and zero if the critter is ambivalent to humans. (Made up numbers). <br>
<br>
Anecdotal support would come from the fact (though I'm not 100% certain on this, been a while) that a long time ago before they massively extended the min-to-max range, certain race/religion combos could not GET highly favourable cons to certain NPCs before maxing/rolling over.<br>
<br>
That, if true, would also explain your observation without invoking charisma.  The only way to test this would be numbers of kills to go from indiff to amiable,  say rather than starting from min/max (or numbers of kills on 1 character with/without charisma buffs).  <br>
<br>
If charisma truely plays a role in amplifying faction gain/loss that would be one of the most horrendous imbalances in game mechanics I'e seen. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ukezzek.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kezzek</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/smallPadlock.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Retired Asst. Admin</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/6/02 11:02:49 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22091.topic&index=28>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A thought</span><hr size=1> Based on the last two nights of fighting in Nurga on Test, some observations:<br>
<br>
-- Nurga is supposedly being overhauled.  It's not itemized yet.  It's almost all coin and some fine steel.  Heckuva lot of coin though.<br>
<br>
-- Re-spawn rates are extremely quick.  A handful of minutes at most.  We were able to comfortably grind in the first room easily.  Pulls were a matter of a few yards.<br>
<br>
-- I probably shouldn't tell you this but the experience is <i>insane</i>.  I think they are still tweaking it.  I gained 5 yellows in 2 nights at level 52/53.  A guildmember went through level 50 in one and a half nights.  I expect this will change soon.  It *can't* stay the same.  I could hit 60 in two weeks at this rate.<br>
<br>
-- The mobs are light hitters (130 dmg) and miss a lot.  Noticeably more misses.<br>
<br>
-- The mobs do not see invis, so as a rogue, I was able to tour the entire premises unmolested.  I can't believe how many named mobs are in there.  I have no idea what they drop or what they will drop after revamp.<br>
<br>
<br>
Disclaimers:  This is Test server.  For all I know, this stuff existed before hand.  Our group didn't fight our way through Nurga because we were on an experience grind (though we plan to this Friday).  Most mobs conned blue to me at 52 with some greenies so perhaps the mob levels haven't been tweaked yet--though my instinct tells me they have.  <b>I'm sure the dungeon is going through more changes.  Certainly, it still needs to be itemized.</b><br>
<br>
<br>
Just fyi stuff. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showPrevMessage?topicID=22091.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showNextMessage?topicID=22091.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22091.topic&index=28><img src=http://www.thesafehouse.org/images/reply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.emailToFriend?topicID=22091.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.threadControl?topicID=22091.topic><img src=http://www.thesafehouse.org/images/dagger.jpg border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=22091.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=22091.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub35.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="thesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion">Main Lounge<option value="thesafehousecontractsbountiesjobsquestsetc">News Bulletin<option value="thesafehousetrainingstudioqaforn